    "description_long": "This object is a standard urban traffic light mounted on a vertical pole. The main housing is a rectangular black box with three circular signal lights arranged vertically: red at the top, yellow in the middle, and green at the bottom. Each light is set within a slightly protruding visor to shield it from sunlight and improve visibility. The pole is cylindrical and appears to be made of metal, supporting the signal box securely. The surface of the housing is matte and slightly textured, typical of weather-resistant outdoor equipment. No pedestrian signals or external control boxes are visible on the structure.",
